jQuery is completely written in vanilla javascript

$("h1") - is similar to - document.querySelectorAll("h1");

//We could change the style of h1 like
$("h1").css("font-size","5rem")
//But this is dirty as we are styling in javascript


//So better way to do it
//Lets create a class say .pager and write its properties in css then

//To add
$("h1").addClass("pager");

//To add multiple class
$("h1").addClass("pager1 pager2");

//To see all class list
$("h1").classList();

//To delete any class list
$("h1").removeClass("pager");


//To check whether an object ahas a class
$("h1").hasClass("pager");

//textContent analogue
$("h1").text("Bye");

//innerHtml analogue
$("h1").HTML("<em>BYE</em>")
